I know this is old, but Jeff and Lesley's problem is that the battery may be good but the contacts became corroded. The battery contacts yellow, they are not sealed, and after a short period through 1000s of charge/discharge cycles the trace to the connector oxidizes to a point where it holds current but fails to pass large amounts. Resubmerging the battery and contacts then gently cleaning the connectors in isopropyl, plus a squirt of low contact resistance lubricant helped resolve the problem for me. Part number of the contact layer is TT32001-135 and the assembly number is BE-TT32001-135.
